# CLAUDE.md — <PROJECT_NAME> conventions

Loaded into every Claude Code conversation. Defines what's load-bearing across the project. Step-by-step procedures live in `.claude/agents/` (subagents) and `.claude/commands/` (slash commands):

- `/clean-tasks <milestone>` — generate per-task spec files for a milestone (if missing) and loop the `task-analyzer` subagent + spec-fix application until the analysis returns no HIGH or MEDIUM findings. Pushes any LOWs to each spec's `## Carry-over from task analysis` section. Cap of 5 rounds.
- `/clean-implement <task>` — full Builder → Auditor loop (up to 10 cycles) + security gate. Spawns subagents via `Task`. Auditor-agreement bypass on stop condition 2: when the auditor surfaces a single clear recommendation and the loop controller concurs against the spec + KDRs + locked decisions, the controller stamps it as a locked decision and feeds it to the next Builder cycle as a carry-over AC instead of halting.
- `/auto-implement <task>` — autonomous-mode `/clean-implement` (run inside the Docker sandbox; see `Dockerfile` + `docker-compose.yml`). Extends `/clean-implement` with (a) a **team gate** after the security gate that runs `sr-dev` + `sr-sdet` and conditionally `architect` (alignment required), (b) auto-commit + auto-push to `<DESIGN_BRANCH>`, and (c) hard halt boundaries (no `<MAIN_BRANCH>`, no `<RELEASE_COMMAND>`, no KDR conflict).
- `/queue-pick [<milestone-list>]` — one-shot orchestrator that spawns `roadmap-selector` to pick the next task. Three verdicts: `PROCEED` (recommends `/auto-implement`), `NEEDS-CLEAN-TASKS` (recommends `/clean-tasks` first), `HALT-AND-ASK` (user arbitrates). Does not chain — for fully-autonomous queue draining, use `/autopilot`.
- `/autopilot [<milestone-list>]` — autonomous queue-drain meta-loop. Loops over (queue-pick → clean-tasks-if-needed → auto-implement) until the queue drains, the supplied scope is exhausted, or a halt fires. Reads `.claude/commands/auto-implement.md` and `.claude/commands/clean-tasks.md` and executes their procedures inline. Pre-flight requires `AIW_AUTONOMY_SANDBOX=1`; HARD HALT on the host.
- `/implement <task>` — single Builder pass.
- `/audit <task>` — single Auditor pass.

Subagents:

- `task-analyzer` — read-mostly; deep-analysis pass on freshly-generated or recently-edited task specs.
- `builder` — implements strictly to spec; returns terse report; no self-grading.
- `auditor` — read-only on source code; mandatory architecture + KDR drift check; writes the issue file.
- `security-reviewer` — post-functional-clean threat-model check.
- `dependency-auditor` — manifest changes + artefact-contents pre-publish.
- `architect` — independent architectural judgment + targeted external research (web-search enabled). Used at mid-loop decision points (Trigger A: new-KDR; Trigger B: external-claim verification).
- `roadmap-selector` — picks the next task using sequential default rule + narrow bug-blocker override.
- `sr-dev` — senior code-quality review at autonomous-mode terminal gate.
- `sr-sdet` — senior test-quality + coverage review at autonomous-mode terminal gate.

